        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 2:46PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 246 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm near Buckhead, or near Madison, moving east at 50
mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to ground
lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs and
blowing around of light, unsecured objects, this storm has
also exhibited localized rotation. A brief tornado could
quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Madison, Greensboro, White Plains, Siloam, Buckhead, Veazey, Parks
Mill, Carey, and Swords.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central, north central and east central Georgia.</instruction>
